pullRequest.body:
Unicode characters can be invisible or looking almost identical to other unicode characters. Some of

Add unicode linter which has the capacity to validate used characters and fix common mistakes. In this first form, the linter only flags `\u00A0` (non-breaking space) and replaces it with a normal space. A follow-up PR will deal with extending a whitelist or blacklist.

Everything flagged by this linter can be fixed fully automatically with lake exe lint-style --fix or by commenting bot fix style on the PR.

---

This is the second PR of a series of PRs about unicode characters in Mathlib. The third PR will extend the unicode characters flagged by this linter.

- [ ] depends on: #17129 (part 1)

- part 3: #16215

## Zulip discussions:

- https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/Whitelist.20for.20Unicode.3F
- https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Lean.20specific.20font
- private reviewer stream: "request for speedy review"

Generally, the discussions seemed to show favour for the first two PRs in this series (handling variant selectors & dealing with invisible chars. such as ` ` (`\u00A0`)) while there seems to be still room for discussion about what to do with general unicode characters (whitelist, blacklist, ...)
